ported as 7-day aggregates by starting from the start_date. If the start and end dates are October 1st and October 30th, then the connector will output 5 records: 01 - 06, 07 - 13, 14 - 20, 21 - 27, and 28 - 30 (3 days only). The minimum allowed value for this field is 1, and the maximum is 89. Cannot be used together with time_increment_period.", "exclusiveMinimum": 0}, "action_breakdowns": {"type": "array", "items": {"enum": ["action_canvas_component_name", "action_carousel_card_id", "action_carousel_card_name", "action_destination", "action_device", "action_reaction", "action_target_id", "action_type", "action_video_sound", "action_video_type", "conversion_destination", "matched_persona_id", "matched_persona_name", "signal_source_bucket", "standard_event_content_type"], "title": "ValidActionBreakdowns", "description": "An enumeration."}, "title": "Action Breakdowns", "default": [], "description": "A list of chosen action_breakdowns for action_breakdowns"}, "action_report_time": {"enum": ["conversion", "impression", "mixed"], "type": "string", "title": "Action Report Time", "default": "mixed", "description": "Determines the report time of action stats. For example, if a person saw the ad on Jan 1st but converted on Jan 2nd, when you query the API with action_report_time=impression, you see a conversion on Jan 1st. When you query the API with action_report_time=conversion, you see a conversion on Jan 2nd.", "airbyte_hidden": true}, "insights_job_timeout": {"type": "integer", "title": "Custom Insights Job Timeout", "default": 60, "maximum": 60, "mininum": 10, "description": "The insights job timeout", "exclusiveMinimum": 0}, "time_increment_period": {"allOf": [{"enum": ["daily", "weekly", "monthly"], "type": "string", "title": "TimeIncrementPeriod", "description": "Calendar-aligned time periods for InsightConfig.\\n\\nThese produce calendar-aligned date buckets rather than N-day rolling windows:\\n- daily: equivalent to time_increment=1 (1-day buckets)\\n- weekly: Monday-through-Sunday calendar weeks\\n- monthly: calendar month boundaries (1st to last day)"}], "title": "Time Increment Period", "description": "Calendar-aligned aggregation period for statistics. Use this instead of time_increment to produce consistently aligned time buckets regardless of start_date. 'daily' is equivalent to time_increment=1. 'weekly' aligns to Monday-through-Sunday calendar weeks. 'monthly' aligns to calendar month boundaries (1st to last day of each month) and is natively supported by the Facebook API. Cannot be used together with time_increment."}, "include_incrementality": {"type": "boolean", "title": "Include Incrementality", "default": false, "description": "If enabled, the incrementality attribution window will be included in the action attribution windows for this custom insight. This allows you to retrieve incrementality data for action metrics."}, "insights_lookback_window": {"type": "integer", "title": "Custom Insights Lookback Window", "default": 28, "maximum": 28, "mininum": 1, "description": "The attribution window", "exclusiveMinimum": 0}}, "description": "Config for custom insights"}, "order": 9, "title": "Custom Insights", "description": "A list which contains ad statistics entries, each entry must have a name and can contains fields, breakdowns or action_breakdowns. Click on \\"add\\" to fill this field."}, "campaign_statuses": {"type": "array", "items": {"enum": ["ACTIVE", "ARCHIVED", "DELETED", "IN_PROCESS", "PAUSED", "WITH_ISSUES"], "title": "ValidCampaignStatuses", "description": "An enumeration."}, "order": 4, "title": "Campaign Statuses", "default": [], "description": "Select the statuses you want to be loaded in the stream. If no specific statuses are selected, the API's default behavior applies, and some statuses may be filtered out."}, "insights_job_timeout": {"type": "integer", "order": 12, "title": "Insights Job Timeout", "default": 60, "maximum": 60, "mininum": 10, "description": "Insights Job Timeout establishes the maximum amount of time (in minutes) of waiting for the report job to complete. When timeout is reached the job is considered failed and we are trying to request smaller amount of data by breaking the job to few smaller ones. If you definitely know that 60 minutes is not enough for your report to be processed then you can decrease the timeout value, so we start breaking job to smaller parts faster.", "exclusiveMinimum": 0}, "fetch_thumbnail_images": {"type": "boolean", "order": 7, "title": "Fetch Thumbnail Images from Ad Creative", "default": false, "description": "Set to active if you want to fetch the thumbnail_url and store the result in thumbnail_data_url for each Ad Creative."}, "include_incrementality": {"type": "boolean", "order": 13, "title": "Include Incrementality", "default": false, "description": "If enabled, the incrementality attribution window will be included in the action attribution windows for all built-in insight streams. This allows you to retrieve incrementality data for action metrics. See the Facebook Marketing API documentation for more details: https://developers.facebook.com/docs/marketing-api/reference/ads-action-stats/"}, "insights_lookback_window": {"type": "integer", "order": 11, "title": "Insights Lookback Window", "default": 28, "maximum": 28, "mininum": 1, "description": "The attribution window. Facebook freezes insight data 28 days after it was generated, which means that all data from the past 28 days may have changed since we last emitted it, so you can retrieve refreshed insights from the past by setting this parameter. If you set a custom lookback window value in Facebook account, please provide the same value here.", "exclusiveMinimum": 0}, "action_breakdowns_allow_empty": {"type": "boolean", "title": "Action Breakdowns Allow Empty", "default": true, "description": "Allows action_breakdowns to be an empty list", "airbyte_hidden": true}, "default_ads_insights_action_breakdowns": {"type": "array", "items": {"enum": ["action_canv